<TITLE> 3 Chinese sailors die in shipboard accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 7 (bdnews24.com)  Three Chinese sailors of a foreign ship were found dead Saturday when they fell into one of the ship's tanks, said police and port officials. The Panamanian flag-carrier, Zhong Ye-6, anchored at the port Saturday morning. Police, quoting the ship authorities, said the crewmen had gone down into the ship's tank to clean it. "The sailors fell while cleaning the tank and suffocated to death," said Nizamul Islam, deputy inspector of Patenga Police Station. The relatives of the deceased have been informed and their bodies are being safeguarded, the inspector said. bdnews
